sec.p:
Among all the reactions in e+e− annihilation, e+e−→e+e− and μ+μ− are the two simplest quantum electrodynamics (QED) processes. Calculations of the unpolarized e+e−→e+e− and μ+μ− cross-sections to order α3 (
O ( α ) ∼ 1 %
) correction were studied decades ago[1–4]. Typically, radiative correction includes vertex correction, electron self-energy, vacuum polarization (virtual photon self-energy), and bremsstrahlung [5].
